			<slide id="wittgenstein">
				<title>What is Meaning?</title>
				<blockquote><q href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philosophical_Investigations#Meaning_is_use">The meaning of a word is its use in the language.</q> (<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ludwig_Wittgenstein">Ludwig Wittgenstein</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philosophical_Investigations">Philosophical Investigations</a>, 1953)</blockquote>
				<ul>
					<li>Meaning exists <em>for a purpose</em> and <em>within a context</em></li>
					<li>Communication establishes meaning and makes meaning usable and useful</li>
				</ul>
